fields.name: Brick
fields.description: Small rectangular blocks typically made of fired or sun-dried clay

fields.name: Cardboard
fields.description: Pasteboard or stiff paper

fields.name: Carpet/rug
fields.description: Floor or stair covering made from thick woven fabric

fields.name: Ceramic
fields.description: Hard brittle material produced from nonmetallic minerals by firing at high temperature

fields.name: Concrete
fields.description: Strong hard building material composed of sand and gravel and cement and water

fields.name: Fabric/cloth
fields.description: Artifact made by weaving or felting or knitting or crocheting natural or synthetic fibers

fields.name: Fire
fields.description: Combustion of materials producing heat and light

fields.name: Foliage
fields.description: Plant leaves, flowers, and branches

fields.name: Food
fields.description: Nutritious substance that people or animals eat or drink

fields.name: Fur
fields.description: Short, fine, soft hair of certain animals

fields.name: Glass
fields.description: Hard, brittle substance, typically transparent or translucent

fields.name: Granite
fields.description: Plutonic igneous rock having visibly crystalline texture.  Note that laminate that looks like granite should be labeled as 'Granite'

fields.name: Hair
fields.description: Threadlike strands growing from the skin of people

fields.name: Laminate
fields.description: Composite made of plastic resin and cellulose paper with a decorative finish.  If it is designed to look like another surface, please select that name instead

fields.name: Leather
fields.description: Animal skin made smooth and flexible by removing the hair and then tanning

fields.name: Marble
fields.description: Hard crystalline metamorphic rock that takes a high polish, typically with streaks of color

fields.name: Metal
fields.description: Solid material that is typically hard, shiny, malleable, fusible, and ductile

fields.name: Mirror
fields.description: Polished surface that reflects a clear image

fields.name: Painted
fields.description: Surface covered with a layer of opaque paint (e.g. acrylic or latex paint)

fields.name: Paper/tissue
fields.description: Thin sheets from the pulp of wood or other fibrous substances

fields.name: Plastic - clear
fields.description: Transparent synthetic material made from a wide range of organic polymers (does transmit light)

fields.name: Plastic - opaque
fields.description: Opaque synthetic material made from a wide range of organic polymers (does not transmit light)

fields.name: Rubber/latex
fields.description: Elastic material obtained from the latex sap of trees

fields.name: Skin
fields.description: Thin layer of tissue forming the natural outer covering of the body of a person or animal

fields.name: Sky
fields.description: The atmosphere and outer space as viewed from the earth

fields.name: Sponge
fields.description: Porous mass of interlacing fibers used to absorb water

fields.name: Stone
fields.description: Hard, solid, nonmetallic mineral matter of which rock is made

fields.name: Tile
fields.description: Flat thin rectangular slab used to cover surfaces.  Note that laminate that looks like tile should be labeled as 'Tile'

fields.name: Wallpaper
fields.description: Decorative paper for the walls of rooms

fields.name: Water
fields.description: Liquid found in lakes and rivers

fields.name: Wax
fields.description: Insoluble compounds that are malleable near ambient temperatures

fields.name: Wicker
fields.description: Interlaced slender branches

fields.name: Wood
fields.description: Hard fibrous substance under the bark of trees.  Note that laminate that looks like wood should be labeled as 'Wood'
